						               													<description>Altercation - The Card Slinging Action Game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the game:&amp;#10;Players win the game by either Knocking Out all other players &amp;#10;OR&amp;#10;By being the player with a Vigor Point Total(VPT) Closest to the Target Number (TN) (in either direction) when all cards have been played from the deck and all players hands. *If two players are tied for Closest to TN, The Throwaway Pile gets shuffled and play continues*&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play: &amp;#10;1. Calculate Vigor Point Total (VPT): Roll the 4 dice add the total together: That is each players starting VPT. Write each players name and VPT on the score sheet. &amp;#10;2. Calculate Target Number (TN): Roll 3 dice and add the total. This is the number everyone is trying to get closest to by the end of the game. &amp;#10;3. Decide who plays first. Roll a dice, Flip a coin, etc.  &amp;#10;4. Shuffle the Deck and Deal each Player 5 cards. &amp;#10;5. Place the deck face down in the middle of the table. &amp;#10;6. The first player takes their Turn and play continues to the next player on the left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn:&amp;#10;Step 1: Draw cards until you have 5 in you hand (skip this step on the first turn) &amp;#10;Step 2: Do 1 of the following 2 options: &amp;#10;A. Play a card. Choose a player and play a Lose, Gain, (put this &amp;#10;card in the Throw Away pile next to the deck after addition or &amp;#10;subtraction takes place) or Defender Card (play this card in &amp;#10;front of you) &amp;#10;B. Throw Away  1 Card and Draw 1 new Card &amp;#10;Step 3: End of Turn&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
